		<part id="welcome-track">
			<title>Welcome to the OAI Track!</title>
			<slide id="oai-intro">
				<title>The OpenAPI Initiative (OAI)</title>
				<ul>
					<li>Join the community: <code href="https://github.com/OAI/community" title="OAI Community">github.com/OAI/community</code></li>
					<li>All technical and special interest groups meetings: <code href="https://www.openapis.org/calendar" title="OAI Community Calendar">openapis.org/calendar</code></li>
					<li>Upcoming events (including OAI Tracks): <code href="https://www.openapis.org/events" title="OAI Events">openapis.org/events</code></li>
				</ul>
			</slide>
		</part>
		<part id="oai-user-stories">
			<title>OAI User Stories</title>
			<slide id="wiifm">
				<title><span title="What's in it for me?">WIIFM</span>: Everybody's Favorite Station</title>
				<img src="wiifm.webp" title="WIIFM: What's in it for me?" class="fullsize"/>
			</slide>
			<slide id="wiifm-org-biz">
				<title>WIIFM: Business and Organization Value</title>
				<img src="unbundling-the-enterprise.jpg" title='Stephen Fishman and Matt McLarty, "Unbundling the Enterprise: APIs, Optionality, and the Science of Happy Accidents", 2024' style="float: right ; height : 70% ; margin : 0% 4% 4% 4% ;  filter: drop-shadow(0px 0px 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.6)) ; "/>
				<table cellspacing="20">
					<tr>
						<th align="right" valign="top">As</th>
						<td valign="top">business or organization leader</td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<th align="right" valign="top">I want</th>
						<td valign="top">well-defined and usable digital interfaces for partners and the public</td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<th align="right" valign="top">so that</th>
						<td valign="top">I can more easily change and scale my value streams.</td>
					</tr>
				</table>
			</slide>
			<slide id="wiifm-dev">
				<title>WIIFM: API Developers</title>
				<img src="automating-api-delivery.jpg" title='Ikenna Nwaiwu, " Automating API Delivery: APIOps with OpenAPI", 2024' style="float: right ; height : 70% ; margin : 0% 4% 4% 4% ;  filter: drop-shadow(0px 0px 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.6)) ; "/>
				<table cellspacing="20">
					<tr>
						<th align="right" valign="top">As</th>
						<td valign="top">an API developer</td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<th align="right" valign="top">I want</th>
						<td valign="top">to describe the product I am going to implement</td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<th align="right" valign="top">so that</th>
						<td valign="top">I can use various tools throughout the API lifecycle.</td>
					</tr>
				</table>
			</slide>
			<slide id="wiifm-org-biz">
				<title>WIIFM: API Consumers</title>
				<img src="design-and-build-great-web-apis.jpg" title='Mike Amundsen, "Design and Build Great Web APIs: Robust, Reliable, and Resilient", 2020' style="float: right ; height : 70% ; margin : 0% 4% 4% 4% ;  filter: drop-shadow(0px 0px 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.6)) ; "/>
				<table cellspacing="20">
					<tr>
						<th align="right" valign="top">As</th>
						<td valign="top">an API consumer</td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<th align="right" valign="top">I want</th>
						<td valign="top">APIs to have standardized descriptions</td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<th align="right" valign="top">so that</th>
						<td valign="top">I can easily understand and consume the products I depend on.</td>
					</tr>
				</table>
			</slide>
			<slide id="wiifm-platform">
				<title>WIIFM: Platform Builders</title>
				<img src="platform-strategy.jpg" title='Gregor Hohpe, "Platform Strategy: Innovation Through Harmonization", 2024' style="float: right ; height : 70% ; margin : 0% 4% 4% 4% ;  filter: drop-shadow(0px 0px 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.6)) ; "/>
				<table cellspacing="20">
					<tr>
						<th align="right" valign="top">As</th>
						<td valign="top">an API platform builder</td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<th align="right" valign="top">I want</th>
						<td valign="top">to support standardized description formats</td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<th align="right" valign="top">so that</th>
						<td valign="top">all producers and consumers speak <q>the same language</q>.</td>
					</tr>
				</table>
			</slide>
		</part>
		<part id="ai">
			<title>The 100,000,000,000 lb Gorilla</title>
			<slide id="robots-and-openapi">
				<title>What Does AI Need?</title>
				<img src="robot-reading-openapi-menu.png" class="fullsize"/>
			</slide>
		</part>
		<part id="welcome-versions">
			<title>Welcome New OpenAPI Versions!</title>
			<slide id="openapi-versions">
				<title>Main Versions of OpenAPI</title>
				<ul>
					<li>December 2015: <a href="https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v2.0.html">2.0</a> (previously Swagger 2.0)</li>
					<li>July 2017: <a href="https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.0.html">3.0</a> (currently at <a href="https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.4.html">3.0.4</a>)</li>
					<li>February 2021: <a href="https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.1.0.html">3.1</a> (currently at <a href="https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.1.2.html">3.1.2</a>)</li>
					<li>September 2025: <a href="https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.2.0.html">3.2</a></li>
				</ul>
			</slide>
			<slide id="openapi-3-2-new-features">
				<title>Main New Features of OpenAPI 3.2</title>
				<ul>
					<li>New HTTP methods (including <code>QUERY</code>)</li>
					<li>Enhanced tag system (hierarchical and multiple tags)</li>
					<li>Support for streaming media types</li>
					<li>Updated OAuth support</li>
				</ul>
			</slide>
		</part>
